The K<sub>m</sub> value of ATP for GSK3β, used to calculate the inhibition constants (K of the various compounds, was 20 μM.
Typical Kj values for the compounds of the present invention are in the range of about 0.001 to about 10,000 nM.
Other values for Ki are in the range of about 0.001 to about 1000 nM.
Further values for Ki are in the range of about 0.001 nM to about 300 nM.
